<br>
Just a couple of nights ago, the cleric had to leave and the others were willing to stay after I volunteered to heal.  I asked to move the camp closer to the zoneline just in case.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It was not needed.  We were able to pull steady as I shadow pact (really need to get Auspice), and Corporal Emphathy as needed.  The MT kept the aggro to make it easier for me to heal.  My fingers were a bit tired from life taping, sending in pet, healing, siting and standing and keeping Lich up.  Was it as good as when the cleric was there?  No.  I had to work more.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But the group worked together and we got more xp and loot than we would have if we all had logged.<br>
<br>
This is much different when I aggro kite.  Load up dots to get as much aggro as possible and have pet smack it from behind.  I do this in a group and I would deserve to be kicked out.<br>
<br>
When an enchanter is in group, I put away my emergency mez.<br>
<br>
When the cleric is truly low on mana and I have over 50% mana, you better believe I am twitching the cleric.  I can med during the next pull and I get mana back alot faster.  Usually in time to smack some DD on the mob.  It is nice to have other healers in the group that can heal me and others during the cleric medding.  Makes the down time much slower.<br>
<br>
So for me the biggest challenge is to not get stuck in a rut of playing one way.  You then through in the group dynamics things and it can be really pleasant or really ugly when you don't have the &quot;standard&quot; classes that can do one aspect better than I can. <p>Xsasx Miasma<br>
