<br>
Last night (i'm 57), in PoJ - I was with a 51 shaman and my cleric (now 59), pulled one of the level 60 guards in the lower jails...   Well, as bad timing would have it, I ended up with a level 60 mob, 2 rats AND a minotaur (the room spawn...)<br>
<br>
If I had pulled that when I was 15% mana, I'd have been dead...  (as it was, the three of us ended the fight oom and 60% or less hps...)<br>
<br>
But either way, yes Necro's can pull and do all that other good stuff - but just like other casters, they don't wear plate and they don't have an abundance of hps like melee'rs do...<br>
<br>
They may have a 750 pt rune, but they don't have 4000 hps, a 1000+ AC and they sure can't take a beating of 200 pt hits per hit while trying to FD because with a 150+ defense/dodge/riposte, etc....<br>
