First of all if the headline is correct and someone called a necro useless either that person is one of the dumbest persons on FVie or he had very very bad necros in his group in the past. I used to play a Necro here on FVie waaaaay back when the server was young and I dont think I got denied a group once. Basicly it all comes to your playing stylee as Xsasx said before. You can basicly do anything with a necro. Hell ive been only caster with 5 melees in expgroups with me doing the healing, slowing and the crowd control. There is a few things I never do however....like someone mentioned earlier.<br>
<br>
&quot;What people have to keep in mind that mana dumpin is not cheap eg takes 400 mana away from you and gives 150 mana to the target. <br>
Trying to do that in an xp group is simply not going to work, necro will be oom almost constantly by twitch, so sitting on your butt waiting to get mana just to give to someone, now what fun is that&quot;<br>
<br>
This used to be my biggest concern, ending up in groups who thought this was a necros duty. I met some terrible people who basicly thought this was the purpose of the necro in the group. I had a cleric nuking 2-3 times per mob and asking me to twitch him every mob since he was lom......<br>
Send in pet and twitch me, thats like all the spells you get that aint solospells right?....Yeah sure.<br>
If a cleric/chanter/whatever cant keep the mana up in a expgroup without twitches then he aint going to fit in the group/at the place you hunt at. Ofcourse there are special occasions where the twitch is very good (bad pulls where the cleric/chanter have a risk of going oom, some raids etc etc) but you should almost never have to use the twitch in a exp group with good pulls.<br>
I play monk/cleric today, we are 3 rl friends 2-boxing a full group which is very fun and very rewarding but damn I miss the necro basicly all the time due to the skillfactor involved. Playing a necro to perfection or as close as you are capable of is the hardest thing EQ provides. Atleast the hardest and funniest Ive done, and I basicly tried it all. Well cept roleplaying <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Everything from soloing /duoing /grouping /raiding (Done highend raiding with 5 diffrent toons playing 5 diffrent classes now, all in top guilds at the time) and the funniest and most challenging is to play the necro.<br>
I congratulate all of you who decided to start a necro, highend necro is sooo thx~<br>
<br>
And take care all,<br>
